The paper presents a reinforcement learning algorithm with improvements to the existing HER algorithm. The algorithm is designed to address the issue of sparse reward functions, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The paper focuses on improving the sample efficiency and success rate of the algorithm in challenging environments. Given the focus on reinforcement learning and machine learning, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also presents empirical results in two environments, which suggests a focus on practical applications, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to build the environments, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
